"{\"uid\": \"abc.net.au-listen-programs-worldtoday-australia-smashes-olympic-medal-record-104083308\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Program:The World Today  Presented by  The Paris Olympics are now officially Australia's best games ever, after spectacular performances delivered four gold medals and two bronze in a record-breaking day of competition.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 77, \"end\": 86, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.610031761418943, \"rank\": 0.6244993777422319, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Former Qantas boss Alan Joyce has his payout cut by nearly $10million, following a series of scandals under his reign.\", \"from\": 221, \"to\": 339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 228, \"end\": 234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qantas\", \"score\": 0.9999999999971578, \"rank\": 2.8171263653595957e-12, \"text\": \"Qantas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qantas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qantas\"}, {\"begin\": 240, \"end\": 250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Joyce\", \"score\": 0.9999999382719144, \"rank\": 6.172794740725221e-08, \"text\": \"Alan Joyce\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13414980\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Joyce\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Joyce\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And after a week of rioting in the UK, thousands take to the streets to oppose the anti-immigrant unrest.\", \"from\": 341, \"to\": 446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 376, \"end\": 378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999776091913175, \"rank\": 1.957481673747298e-05, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephanie Smail:Hello and welcome to The World Today.\", \"from\": 448, \"to\": 501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 448, \"end\": 457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\", \"score\": 0.9417632351312262, \"rank\": 0.06165517563617786, \"text\": \"Stephanie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\"}, {\"begin\": 458, \"end\": 463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\", \"score\": 0.9999992977382327, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Smail\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's Thursday the 8th of August.\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am Stephanie Smale coming to you from the lands of the Turrbul and Yugera people in Brisbane.\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 540, \"end\": 549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\", \"score\": 0.9417632351312262, \"rank\": 0.06165517563617786, \"text\": \"Stephanie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\"}, {\"begin\": 592, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turrbal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Turrbul\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turrbal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turrbal\"}, {\"begin\": 621, \"end\": 629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.9996325253897719, \"rank\": 0.00034654543139638115, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, bumpy landing.\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Former Qantas boss Alan Joyce has his payout cut by nearly $10 million, following an internal review at the carrier.\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 660, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qantas\", \"score\": 0.9999999999971578, \"rank\": 2.8171263653595957e-12, \"text\": \"Qantas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qantas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qantas\"}, {\"begin\": 672, \"end\": 682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Joyce\", \"score\": 0.9999999382719144, \"rank\": 6.172794740725221e-08, \"text\": \"Alan Joyce\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13414980\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Joyce\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Joyce\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And after a week of rioting in the UK, thousands take to the streets to oppose the anti-immigrant unrest.\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 805, \"end\": 807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999776091913175, \"rank\": 1.957481673747298e-05, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Opinion:We are not going to let fascists, we are not going to let racists and the far right march here.\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephanie Smail:The Paris Olympics are now officially Australia's best games ever, with spectacular performances delivering four gold medals and two bronze in a record-breaking day of competition.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1178, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 982, \"end\": 991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\", \"score\": 0.9417632351312262, \"rank\": 0.06165517563617786, \"text\": \"Stephanie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\"}, {\"begin\": 992, \"end\": 997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\", \"score\": 0.9999992977382327, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Smail\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\"}, {\"begin\": 1036, \"end\": 1045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.610031761418943, \"rank\": 0.6244993777422319, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From the ancient sport of pole vaulting to the more modern art of skateboarding, Australia's athletes have pushed the team to third position on the medal tally.\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1260, \"end\": 1269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.6033408283936308, \"rank\": 0.3615086171347151, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To take us through the results and the celebrations, here's Rachel Mealey.\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1400, \"end\": 1406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Berry\", \"score\": 0.580935446750402, \"rank\": 0.38568299833102787, \"text\": \"Rachel\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Berry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Berry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rachel Mealey:In the wee hours, Australians like Tess Jenkins watched as pole vaulter Nina Kennedy took the nation to new heights of sporting success.\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1502, \"end\": 1514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.9999990214819503, \"rank\": 9.785149006013977e-07, \"text\": \"Nina Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As she soared over the 4.9 metre high bar, Nina Kennedy says she knew it was enough to win.\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1610, \"end\": 1622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.9999990214819503, \"rank\": 9.785149006013977e-07, \"text\": \"Nina Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nina Kennedy:Pole vault's an interesting one because when you clear the bar you just want to let loose and you want to celebrate but you know in the back of my mind I knew these girls were not going to give up easily and I might have to jump higher so it's about celebrating but switching back on and keeping that focus.\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1660, \"end\": 1672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.9999990214819503, \"rank\": 9.785149006013977e-07, \"text\": \"Nina Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rachel Mealey:She says competing in front of a crowd of 70,000 intensified the stress of the event.\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 2081, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nina Kennedy:I think we all knew the winner was going to be the person that could handle the stress of the Olympic Games the best.\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2213, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is such a mental event.\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2240, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rachel Mealey:Nina Kennedy's medal set a new record for Australia with 18 gold medals.\", \"from\": 2242, \"to\": 2328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2242, \"end\": 2248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Green\", \"score\": 0.5392725976134567, \"rank\": 0.44590746715024376, \"text\": \"Rachel\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Green\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Green\"}, {\"begin\": 2256, \"end\": 2268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.9999990214819503, \"rank\": 9.785149006013977e-07, \"text\": \"Nina Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier Australian skateboarder Keegan Palmer won his second successive Olympic gold medal at the Men's Park Final.\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2337, \"end\": 2347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9765540941988822, \"rank\": 0.01435232531429719, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 2361, \"end\": 2374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keegan Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 21-year-old set the benchmark in the first of his three runs with a score of 93.11, holding off his nearest rivals.\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2564, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Keegan Palmer:Actually surprisingly enough the first run was more of a safety run to be honest and my last two runs I really wanted to go for some new tricks that I have been holding on to and practicing but sadly fell off in the middle of the run so I did not really get to get to them but you know we were able to hold on to it with the first run so we definitely take it.\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2940, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2566, \"end\": 2579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keegan Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rachel Mealey:His victory followed another skateboarding medal from 14-year-old Arisa Trew who won gold yesterday in the Women's Park Final.\", \"from\": 2942, \"to\": 3082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2942, \"end\": 2948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Green\", \"score\": 0.5392725976134567, \"rank\": 0.44590746715024376, \"text\": \"Rachel\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Green\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Green\"}, {\"begin\": 3022, \"end\": 3027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\", \"score\": 0.999999999947363, \"rank\": 5.263035239506222e-11, \"text\": \"Arisa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Keegan Palmer says today's gold was a sweet victory.\", \"from\": 3083, \"to\": 3135, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3083, \"end\": 3096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keegan Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Keegan Palmer:Dude yeah that was one really crazy feeling that's for sure.\", \"from\": 3137, \"to\": 3211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3137, \"end\": 3150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keegan Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was an absolute honour to be able to skate with all my friends that I have known for the plus 10 years and you know it was emotional slash you know just excited like who would have thought like just the gold was a two-time Olympian and you know now we are a two-time gold medalist it does not really get much better than me and especially on the day Australia's had today we broke our record and to be able to be a part of that it's just incredible.\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3664, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3438, \"end\": 3446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999908622534386, \"rank\": 9.132139909165633e-06, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rachel Mealey:Whether it was on land or on water Australians owned the day.\", \"from\": 3666, \"to\": 3741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3666, \"end\": 3672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Berry\", \"score\": 0.8628308286110816, \"rank\": 0.12609936583275128, \"text\": \"Rachel\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Berry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Berry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"West Australian sailor Matt Wearn also won back-to-back gold in the Men's dinghy competition.\", \"from\": 3742, \"to\": 3835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3747, \"end\": 3757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9998214112882444, \"rank\": 0.00011508973582497977, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Matt Wearn:These words can not really describe it really it's um yeah pretty phenomenal it's just incredible to be able to go go back to back and bring home a second gold medal.\", \"from\": 3837, \"to\": 4014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rachel Mealey:Australia has now taken out that title for the fourth consecutive Olympics.\", \"from\": 4016, \"to\": 4105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Matt Wern navigated tricky conditions to seal the win.\", \"from\": 4106, \"to\": 4160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4111, \"end\": 4115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wern\", \"score\": 0.9999999097831319, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wern\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wern\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wern\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Matt Wearn:Just super super variable so there is a lot of clouds going over which is changing the wind a lot a lot of direction changes and strength changes so um yeah it just sort of come and go and yeah it was starting to look like we were not going to get a race in again today which um which makes it hard to deal with but yeah we managed to do it and yeah it was really really good.\", \"from\": 4162, \"to\": 4549, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rachel Mealey:In track cycling Australia claimed gold in the men's team pursuit for the first time since the Athens Olympics 20 years ago.\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4689, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4551, \"end\": 4557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Berry\", \"score\": 0.8977004999155902, \"rank\": 0.0767734943787355, \"text\": \"Rachel\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Berry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Berry\"}, {\"begin\": 4582, \"end\": 4591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.6989253638424824, \"rank\": 0.26806181539773, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a blur of speed Sam Welsford, Oliver Bleddyn, Connor Leahy and Kelland O'Brien held off Great Britain to take the win.\", \"from\": 4690, \"to\": 4811, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4709, \"end\": 4721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Welsford\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Welsford\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Welsford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Welsford\"}, {\"begin\": 4730, \"end\": 4737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bleddyn_ap_Cynfyn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bleddyn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bleddyn_ap_Cynfyn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bleddyn_ap_Cynfyn\"}, {\"begin\": 4739, \"end\": 4745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Connor_MacLeod\", \"score\": 0.9744143547710359, \"rank\": 0.02625735340797837, \"text\": \"Connor\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Connor_MacLeod\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Connor_MacLeod\"}, {\"begin\": 4746, \"end\": 4751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Leahy\", \"score\": 0.9234383258843782, \"rank\": 0.08290914392435743, \"text\": \"Leahy\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Leahy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Leahy\"}, {\"begin\": 4756, \"end\": 4771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelland_O'Brien\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kelland O'Brien\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelland_O'Brien\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelland_O'Brien\"}, {\"begin\": 4781, \"end\": 4794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.6644389448038402, \"rank\": 0.2950542294009988, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Darren Casey is from the Bendigo and District Cycling Club.\", \"from\": 4812, \"to\": 4871, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4819, \"end\": 4824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Demons\", \"score\": 0.9999687293902438, \"rank\": 1.9784687583545363e-05, \"text\": \"Casey\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Demons\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Demons\"}, {\"begin\": 4837, \"end\": 4844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bendigo\", \"score\": 0.999782675471422, \"rank\": 0.00020584186755051356, \"text\": \"Bendigo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bendigo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bendigo\"}, {\"begin\": 4858, \"end\": 4865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycle_sport\", \"score\": 0.9888890288444496, \"rank\": 0.008057664068468829, \"text\": \"Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycle_sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycle_sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He says he watched in awe.\", \"from\": 4872, \"to\": 4898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Darren Casey:Kel is just a real professional he's uh he's the starter of the pursuit team so he does probably the bulk of the power to get the speed up you know like they are sitting on 65, 70 kilometers per hour.\", \"from\": 4900, \"to\": 5113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So Kel is also a pro tour rider so he lives in Spain so he's got to juggle being a pro tour rider same as Sam Welsford and also a track rider so it's a it's a real juggling act and for him to to get in form a condition to swap from you know 200, 250 kilometer road races and actually get a gold medal is impressive in its own right.\", \"from\": 5114, \"to\": 5446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5161, \"end\": 5166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.7303826361800092, \"rank\": 0.33745153100665803, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}, {\"begin\": 5220, \"end\": 5232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Welsford\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Welsford\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Welsford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Welsford\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rachel Mealey:As celebrations continue in Paris back in Sydney Prime Minister Anthony Albanese says the athletes have earned the accolades of the nation.\", \"from\": 5448, \"to\": 5601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5448, \"end\": 5454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Berry\", \"score\": 0.8977004999155902, \"rank\": 0.0767734943787355, \"text\": \"Rachel\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Berry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Berry\"}, {\"begin\": 5490, \"end\": 5495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999674132346144, \"rank\": 3.258782723523433e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"t