st inflicting damage.\", \"from\": 20347, \"to\": 20444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20347, \"end\": 20353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Declan_Napier\", \"score\": 0.9630258577306077, \"rank\": 0.03296771788687422, \"text\": \"Declan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Declan_Napier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Declan_Napier\"}, {\"begin\": 20360, \"end\": 20373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Davis_(ornithologist)\", \"score\": 0.999996380754011, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Malcolm Davis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Davis_(ornithologist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Davis_(ornithologist)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Malcolm Davis:My guess is that the Ukrainians would then try to reinforce their position to hold onto the captured territory.\", \"from\": 20446, \"to\": 20571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20446, \"end\": 20459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Davis_(ornithologist)\", \"score\": 0.999996380754011, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Malcolm Davis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Davis_(ornithologist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Davis_(ornithologist)\"}, {\"begin\": 20481, \"end\": 20491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainians\", \"score\": 0.7610240989192457, \"rank\": 0.3139899118342534, \"text\": \"Ukrainians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Declan Gooch:What might be the overarching strategy here?\", \"from\": 20573, \"to\": 20630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20573, \"end\": 20579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Declan_Napier\", \"score\": 0.9630258577306077, \"rank\": 0.03296771788687422, \"text\": \"Declan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Declan_Napier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Declan_Napier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Malcolm Davis:The broader strategy is to try and deny the Russians essentially sanctuaries from which they can attack Ukraine.\", \"from\": 20632, \"to\": 20758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20690, \"end\": 20698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russians\", \"score\": 0.45247584354323606, \"rank\": 0.758712771753936, \"text\": \"Russians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russians\"}, {\"begin\": 20750, \"end\": 20757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.833148761544496, \"rank\": 0.13941653464814002, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If this offensive is successful, then the Ukrainians will control some key areas of territory inside Russia that is then denied to the Russians.\", \"from\": 20759, \"to\": 20903, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20801, \"end\": 20811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainians\", \"score\": 0.7610240989192457, \"rank\": 0.3139899118342534, \"text\": \"Ukrainians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainians\"}, {\"begin\": 20860, \"end\": 20866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9727069836514138, \"rank\": 0.013802676076655964, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 20894, \"end\": 20902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russians\", \"score\": 0.45247584354323606, \"rank\": 0.758712771753936, \"text\": \"Russians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Declan Gooch:While it's unlikely to represent a major turning point in the war, he says it will have political implications for Vladimir Putin.\", \"from\": 20905, \"to\": 21048, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21033, \"end\": 21047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 0.9999999999998863, \"rank\": 1.4607675585999587e-13, \"text\": \"Vladimir Putin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Malcolm Davis:Obviously, it's a humiliation for him.\", \"from\": 21050, \"to\": 21102, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not see him being overthrown as a result of this, but he's more likely to be a little bit more reckless in terms of how he responds.\", \"from\": 21103, \"to\": 21240, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He could potentially escalate elsewhere.\", \"from\": 21241, \"to\": 21281, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephanie Smail:Malcolm Davis from the Australian Strategic Policy Institute, ending that report by Declan Gooch.New research shows the waters around the Great Barrier Reef have hit their hottest summer temperatures in 400 years.\", \"from\": 21283, \"to\": 21512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21283, \"end\": 21292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Scully\", \"score\": 0.9975247106076267, \"rank\": 0.0019710546441587427, \"text\": \"Stephanie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Scully\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Scully\"}, {\"begin\": 21293, \"end\": 21298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\", \"score\": 0.9999992977382327, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Smail\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\"}, {\"begin\": 21299, \"end\": 21312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Davis_(ornithologist)\", \"score\": 0.999996380754011, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Malcolm Davis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Davis_(ornithologist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Davis_(ornithologist)\"}, {\"begin\": 21322, \"end\": 21359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Strategic_Policy_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian Strategic Policy Institute\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Strategic_Policy_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Strategic_Policy_Institute\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Scientists say climate change is to blame and they are calling for more action to protect the World Heritage-listed region.\", \"from\": 21513, \"to\": 21636, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Elizabeth Cramsie reports.\", \"from\": 21637, \"to\": 21663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21637, \"end\": 21646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.9915418991302959, \"rank\": 0.007381416524945077, \"text\": \"Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elizabeth Cramsie:Alan Wallish has been operating Great Barrier Reef tours from Cairns for over 35 years and the founder and director of Passions of Paradise says conditions appear as good as he's ever seen them.\", \"from\": 21665, \"to\": 21877, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21665, \"end\": 21674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.9915418991302959, \"rank\": 0.007381416524945077, \"text\": \"Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}, {\"begin\": 21745, \"end\": 21751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cairns\", \"score\": 0.7777513998941125, \"rank\": 0.2841114108425194, \"text\": \"Cairns\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cairns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cairns\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alan Wallish:It is very colourful, it appears to be in a very, very healthy condition.\", \"from\": 21879, \"to\": 21965, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So we suffered very little bleaching off the Cairns Port Douglas region this year and what we did have a little bit, it has recovered but overall the reef is looking in really good condition.\", \"from\": 21966, \"to\": 22157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22011, \"end\": 22017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cairns\", \"score\": 0.7777513998941125, \"rank\": 0.2841114108425194, \"text\": \"Cairns\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cairns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cairns\"}, {\"begin\": 22018, \"end\": 22030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_Douglas\", \"score\": 0.999999995688313, \"rank\": 4.311661439555522e-09, \"text\": \"Port Douglas\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_Douglas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_Douglas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elizabeth Cramsie:But scientists say the habitat is being pushed closer to a tipping point from which it may not recover.\", \"from\": 22159, \"to\": 22280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"New research shows under the surface temperatures are the warmest they have been in 400 years.\", \"from\": 22281, \"to\": 22375, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Ben Henley:Our study shows that the recent events are very extreme in that long-term context and we also use climate models to confirm that climate change is responsible for the warming and extreme high sea surface temperature events.\", \"from\": 22377, \"to\": 22614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22384, \"end\": 22390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henley_Royal_Regatta\", \"score\": 0.7171301049290255, \"rank\": 0.3939953098385945, \"text\": \"Henley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henley_Royal_Regatta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henley_Royal_Regatta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elizabeth Cramsie:That's Dr Ben Henley from the University of Wollongong.\", \"from\": 22616, \"to\": 22689, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22648, \"end\": 22654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henley_Royal_Regatta\", \"score\": 0.7171301049290255, \"rank\": 0.3939953098385945, \"text\": \"Henley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henley_Royal_Regatta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henley_Royal_Regatta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's the lead researcher.\", \"from\": 22690, \"to\": 22715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The study focused on periods from January to March using already published records from coral colonies.\", \"from\": 22716, \"to\": 22819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Ben Henley:And these are cores that are drilled into these coral colonies and the chemistry, the chemical signatures that are laid down at the time the coral was growing, the coral surface is alive and the interior of the coral colony is a dead skeleton.\", \"from\": 22821, \"to\": 23078, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22828, \"end\": 22834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henley_Royal_Regatta\", \"score\": 0.7171301049290255, \"rank\": 0.3939953098385945, \"text\": \"Henley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henley_Royal_Regatta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henley_Royal_Regatta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They record the temperature and other environmental conditions at the time it's growing so we can take those cores back to the lab and our colleagues over the previous decades from around the region have published these fantastic records, some of them at very high resolution, going back in time for up to 400 years or so.\", \"from\": 23079, \"to\": 23401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Elizabeth Cramsie:And the results were so shocking he had to check them twice.\", \"from\": 23403, \"to\": 23481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Ben Henley:I had to actually plot it again and have a careful check of the year because it was just so extreme it really just jumped off the top of the graph.\", \"from\": 23483, \"to\": 23644, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the warmest on record in the last 400 years.\", \"from\": 23645, \"to\": 23695, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Elizabeth Cramsie:He says while good work is being done, the reef needs more.\", \"from\": 23697, \"to\": 23774, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Ben Henley:We have to deal with climate change and it's the long term driver of the risk to the reef.\", \"from\": 23776, \"to\": 23880, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Elizabeth Cramsie:Dr Lissa Schindler is from the Australian Marine Conservation Society.\", \"from\": 23882, \"to\": 23970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23903, \"end\": 23908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leszno\", \"score\": 0.9999999979962695, \"rank\": 1.401571478547451e-09, \"text\": \"Lissa\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leszno\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leszno\"}, {\"begin\": 23931, \"end\": 23969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Marine_Conservation_Society\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian Marine Conservation Society\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Marine_Conservation_Society\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Marine_Conservation_Society\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Lissa Schindler:It was the highest and most prolonged and extreme temperatures that the Great Barrier Reef has experienced and that's why we saw such huge impact from a bleaching perspective.\", \"from\": 23972, \"to\": 24166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Elizabeth Cramsie:Alan Wallish says it's not all doom and gloom but ensuring the ongoing health of the reef will take a combined effort.\", \"from\": 24168, \"to\": 24304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alan Wallish:The Great Barrier Reef is not one thing.\", \"from\": 24306, \"to\": 24359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a huge living organism that's over 2000km long and what happens on one section might not necessarily happen on another.\", \"from\": 24360, \"to\": 24484, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a little bit of a canary in the coal mine.\", \"from\": 24485, \"to\": 24533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So we do want to protect our precious resource here and we need to be working together, science, tourism operators, the communities, traditional owners etc.\", \"from\": 24534, \"to\": 24690, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is an all encompassing thing that we need to do.\", \"from\": 24691, \"to\": 24744, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephanie Smail:Great Barrier Reef tour operator Alan Wallish ending that report by Elizabeth Cramsie.\", \"from\": 24746, \"to\": 24848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 24746, \"end\": 24755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\", \"score\": 0.9875563425449132, \"rank\": 0.011253201848390477, \"text\": \"Stephanie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\"}, {\"begin\": 24756, \"end\": 24761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\", \"score\": 0.9999992977382327, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Smail\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\"}, {\"begin\": 24830, \"end\": 24839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.9888688434910875, \"rank\": 0.01023332776670064, \"text\": \"Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's all from the World Today team.\", \"from\": 24849, \"to\": 24890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thanks for your company.\", \"from\": 24891, \"to\": 24915, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am Stephanie Smail.\", \"from\": 24916, \"to\": 24937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 24921, \"end\": 24930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\", \"score\": 0.9875563425449132, \"rank\": 0.011253201848390477, \"text\": \"Stephanie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\"}, {\"begin\": 24931, \"end\": 24936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\", \"score\": 0.9999992977382327, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Smail\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smail\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Published:17h agoTue 2 Dec 2025 at 1:00am  Published:YesterdayMon 1 Dec 2025 at 1:00am  Published:FriFri 28 Nov 2025 at 1:30am  Published:ThuThu 27 Nov 2025 at 1:30am  Download the ABC listen app to hear more of your favourite podcasts  We acknowledge Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples as the     First Australians and Traditional Custodians of the lands where we     live, learn and work.\", \"from\": 24939, \"to\": 25340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 25120, \"end\": 25123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.9999982286753719, \"rank\": 1.7713246421439148e-06, \"text\": \"ABC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http: